# Files excluded from the per-file Go coverage gate (cmd/coverage-gate).
#
# Keep this list SHORT and principled. Only exclude code that genuinely cannot
# or should not be unit-tested, mirroring how web/vitest.config.ts excludes the
# service-worker shell and the test/ harness. "Hard to test" is not a reason to
# exclude: those files are the work item for issue #103, not exemptions.
#
# Syntax (matched against repo-relative paths):
#   path/to/file.go   exact file
#   path/prefix/      directory and everything beneath it (note trailing slash)
#   internal/*/x.go   filepath.Match glob

# Test infrastructure: exercised only by other tests, so it has no tests of its
# own (the parallel to vitest excluding src/test/**).
internal/testsupport/

# The coverage gate tool itself: a thin CLI entrypoint added for this very gate.
cmd/coverage-gate/main.go

# One-shot ops CLI for relabelling flight parts. Its pure logic (tableRelabel,
# isQuotaExhausted, sleep) IS unit-tested, but run()'s core re-resolve loop is
# hardwired to providers.NewAeroDataBox (the live RapidAPI host, with no
# endpoint/resolver injection point), so the loop can't be exercised without
# either calling the real flight API or adding a production seam to an
# entrypoint purely for coverage. Excluded on that basis, not mere difficulty.
# (cmd/server/main.go is deliberately NOT excluded: its wiring proved testable
# and it sits at ~97%.)
cmd/backfill-flight-labels/main.go
